System Requirements:
--------------------

Lipsia is tested for the following operating systems (32bit):

- Debian Lenny 32bit and 64bit

- Debian Squeeze 32bit and 64bit

- Debian Wheezy 32bit and 64bit

- Ubuntu Hardy 32bit and 64bit

- Ubuntu Jaunty 32bit and 64bit

- Ubuntu Lucid 32bit and 64bit

- Ubuntu Natty 32bit and 64bit

- In order to use Lipsia on other Linux systems, the sources must be downloaded and compiled


The following packages must be installed
----------------------------------------

- medical data integration toolkit (ISIS)

- ISIS plugin for vista files (isisio0-vista)

- ISIS python bridge (isis-python)

- Volumetric Image Analysis 2.0 (VIA)

- Gnu Scientific Library (GSL)

- Fast Fourier Transform West (FFTW3)

- ATLAS library (CPU specific)


Further system requirements:
----------------------------

- QT 3 with multithread and OpenGL support

- Xorg with OpenGL support

- If necessary, compatibility packages for libstdc++

- If necessary, compatibility packages for qt 3

Optional requirements:
----------------------

- ISIS plugin for nifti files (isisio0-nifti)

- ISIS plugin for dicom files (isisio0-dicom)

- ISIS plugin for tar files (isisio0-tar-proxy)

- ISIS plugin for gz files (isisio0-gz-proxy)

- ISIS plugin for raw files (isisio0-raw)

- ISIS plugin for png files (isisio0-png)
